<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">âThough the fervor among private equity groups to buy into defense contracting has dimmed, there remain investors interested in the market. Some contracting executives are <b>forecasting that 2014 could be the bottom for sales</b>, meaning investors may take a chance on buying at lower prices now, hoping for an upswing in the coming years.â</p>
